You’re mixing two scopes:

- `round.set(roundIndex, i)` writes to the **Round** scope.
- `p.round.get(roundIndex)` reads from the **PlayerRound** scope.

Those are different. A value set on `round` is **not** visible on `p.round` unless you copy it there. That’s why `p.round.get(roundIndex)` was `undefined` earlier.

Also, small correction: Empirica has **many stages per round**, not many rounds per stage. A `stage` belongs to exactly one `round`. So it’s fine to use the current round’s index during `onStageStart`.

