Yep — in Empirica the **game can start before any players join**, so `onGameStart` often runs with `game.players` empty. That’s why your per-player shuffles sometimes don’t exist later.

You’ve got two solid ways to guarantee “each player gets a private shuffle before they play”:

# Option A (best): initialize when the player joins
If your version exposes a player callback (often named something like `onPlayerCreated` / `onPlayerJoined`), do the per-player init there—this fires before they enter Round 1:

```js
