Ah—then what’s happening is you’re reading from a source that isn’t changing the way you expect. On the server, `game.currentRound` can lag (it reflects the game’s *global* “current” round and only changes after the previous round fully ends). That’s why you keep seeing `0` during your `choice*` stages.

You’ve got three robust ways to get the correct index without relying on that:

## Option 1 (cleanest): stamp the index on each Stage at creation
Do this once when you build the stages, then read it directly from `stage`:

```js
// when creating stages
function addStageWithIdx(round, name, duration, idx) {
  const st = round.addStage({ name, duration });
  st.set(roundIndex, idx);
  return st;
}
```

Then:

```js
