## Option 3 (zero refactor): derive the index by locating the Round
If you don’t want to change your creation code right now, compute it on the fly:

```js
Empirica.onStageStart(({ stage, game }) => {
  const r = stage.currentRound || game.currentRound; // whichever exists
  if (!r) return;

  const rounds = game.rounds || []; // Empirica exposes the round list
  const roundIndex = rounds.findIndex(R => R.id === r.id);
  if (roundIndex < 0) {
    console.warn(Could not locate round in game.rounds);
    return;
  }

