ahhh perfect — that tracks. In Empirica, `roundIndex` was your own custom field (only set if you explicitly `round.set(roundIndex, i)`), whereas **`index` is a built-in** on rounds/stages:

- `stage.currentRound.index` → the round’s 0-based position in `game.rounds`
- `stage.index` → the stage’s 0-based position within its round

So switching to `index` works because it’s always populated by the framework, while `roundIndex` wasn’t guaranteed to exist.

### safest way to read it
```js
Empirica.onStageStart(({ stage }) => {
  const roundObj = stage.currentRound;
  const roundIndex =
    (roundObj && typeof roundObj.index === number && roundObj.index) ??
    (roundObj?.get?.(index)) ?? 0; // fallback if your build exposes it via get()

  // if you instead want the stage's position within the round:
  const stageIndex =
    (typeof stage.index === number && stage.index) ??
    (stage.get?.(index)) ?? 0;

  // ...use roundIndex for per-round selection...
});
```

